Mark MacSymon, CFP® of Private Client Holdings, shares his insight on how to build a resilient investment strategy. – What is meant by a resilient investment plan or wealth management strategy?
– How do you optimally determine the overall exposure to various asset classes which combine to form a total investable portfolio?
– Is periodic rebalancing necessary to remain aligned to a strategic asset allocation benchmark or is there room for variance?
– Investors have various lifestyles and investable goals – how is the overall strategy tailored to account for different goals with varying investment time horizons?
– Why is it important to have an investment plan or wealth management strategy in place? Brought to you by the Financial Planning Institute of Southern Africa (FPI).